OL,3,CAnger explodes on welfare with fears
OL,4,C100 MPs could oppose plans
OL,6,FBut what about welfare reforms and
OL,7,Fspecifically a decision to make it
OL,8,Fharder to claim Personal Independence
OL,9,FPayments (PIP), a benefit designed to
OL,10,Fhelp with the cost of disability?
OL,12,FOn that, there is anger too, and
OL,13,Fspread further across the party's left-
OL,14,Fright spectrum than you might imagine,
OL,15,Fwith many MPs signing letters to the
OL,16,FChief Whip or PM himself. Some MPs
OL,17,Fthink as many as 100 colleagues are up
OL,18,Fin arms.
OL,20,FThe question for Downing Street is how
OL,21,Fmany will actually rebel.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/12
