OL,3,CAnger explodes on welfare with fears
OL,4,C100 MPs could oppose plans
OL,6,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,7,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,8,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,9,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,11,FOne of the most reassuring things for
OL,12,Fthem has been that, however rocky
OL,13,Fthings get, Labour's huge majority
OL,14,Fprovides political stability.
OL,16,FBut a senior figure has admitted to
OL,17,Fme, that if a vote on the welfare
OL,18,Fpolicy slated for June was to take
OL,19,Fplace this week, amid this anger, it
OL,20,Fwould likely inflict a bloody nose on
OL,21,FStarmer's administration.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
