OL,3,CAnger explodes on welfare with fears
OL,4,C100 MPs could oppose plans
OL,6,FBut what was striking was the number
OL,7,Fof newer MPs, who have taken over in
OL,8,Fhistorically Tory areas, also raise
OL,9,Fthe alarm.
OL,11,FLizzi Collinge, the new(ish) MP for
OL,12,FMorecambe and Lunesdale, warned that
OL,13,Fwhile welfare needed reform, it should
OL,14,Fnot come at the cost of disabled
OL,15,Fpeople.
