OL,3,CAnger explodes on welfare with fears
OL,4,C100 MPs could oppose plans
OL,6,FOne thing that angers MPs is that the
OL,7,Fcuts to PIP are happening now, while
OL,8,Fthe more positive policies for extra
OL,9,Femployment support are not coming in
OL,10,Ffor years.
OL,12,FWebb had signed up to a statement by
OL,13,FRed Wall MPs that said the Government
OL,14,Fhad fallen short for voters and must
OL,15,Fnow rethink Winter Fuel Payments and
OL,16,Freject "Treasury orthodoxy".
OL,18,FOn that, much of the frustration is
OL,19,Faimed at Rachel Reeves.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
