OL,3,CAnger explodes on welfare with fears
OL,4,C100 MPs could oppose plans
OL,6,FOne MP in a rural Tory facing seat
OL,7,Ftold me: "'For lots of us, the reform
OL,8,Fvote is grabbing headlines, but my
OL,9,Fseat would be put in danger by a
OL,10,Ffracturing of the progressive left
OL,11,Fvote that solidified behind me at the
OL,12,FGE."
OL,14,FThere are some on the right who want a
OL,15,Ftougher line on immigration, others on
OL,16,Fthe left who tell me they see
OL,17,Frightwing Conservatives taking a more
OL,18,Fmoral stand on Gaza.
OL,20,FInside Downing Street, some think the
OL,21,Fdivide is bridgeable.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/12
