OL,3,CAnger explodes on welfare with fears
OL,4,C100 MPs could oppose plans
OL,6,FBut it wasn't the only one - so too
OL,7,Fwas the inheritance tax on farmers.
OL,9,FThe Government thinks that welfare
OL,10,Fchanges are different as they can
OL,11,Fargue they are about the motivation to
OL,12,Fincentivise work, and are popular with
OL,13,Fthe wider public.
OL,15,FMorgan McSweeney - Starmer's chief of
OL,16,Fstaff - has told colleagues it is the
OL,17,Fissue with the most disconnect between
OL,18,Fvoters and Labour members, and he
OL,19,Fwants to be on the side of the former.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/12
